 LAGOS State chapter of the All Progressive Congress (APC) in the United Kingdom (UK) has expressed support for Nigerian youths in their agitation to end police brutality. In a statement by its Chairman, Tayo Shodeinde, the party commiserated with Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu and the families of those who lost loved ones during the #EndSARS unrest, including security officers. “We also reaffirm that we do support an end to SARS and police brutality in Nigeria. However, we also condemn the attack on Police stations, malls, public and private properties by hoodlums who hijacked the protest,” the statement said.A